Sentencas: Recently, semiconductor-ionic materials (SIMs) have emerged as new functional materials, which possessed high ionic conductivity with successful applications as the electrolyte in advanced low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet

Sentencas: In order to reveal the ion-conducting mechanism in SIM, a typical SIM pellet consisted of semiconductor La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) and ionic conductor Sm and Ca Co-doped ceria Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC) are suffered from sintering at different temperatures.
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet

Sentencas: It has been found that the performance of LSCF-SCDC electrolyte fuel cell decreases with the sintering temperature, the cell assembled from LSCF-SCDC pellet sintered at 600 degrees C exhibits a peak power density (P-max) of 543mW/cm(2) at 550 degrees C and also excellent performance of 312mW/cm(2) even at LT (500 degrees C).
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet

Sentencas: On the contrary, devices based on 1000 degrees C pellet presented a poor P-max of 106mW/cm(2).
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet

Sentencas: The performance difference may result from the diverse ionic conductivity of SIM pellet through different temperatures sintering.
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet

Sentencas: The high-temperature sintering could severely destroy the interface between SCDC and LSCF, which provide fast transport pathways for oxygen ions conduction.
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet

Sentencas: Such phenomenon provides direct and strong evidence for the interfacial conduction in LSCF-SCDC SIMs.
Titulo: The sintering temperature effect on electrochemical properties of Ce0.8Sm0.05Ca0.15O2- (SCDC)-La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) heterostructure pellet
